=Description=

"I started this podcast to amplify the voices of those involved in the Occupy Wall Street movement. I share their frustration with our political leaders, our business leaders and the direction of our country. For too long, we have stood silently by as the country’s wealth and power concentrated in the hands of the few. Now it’s time to speak out. This is my contribution to the conversation.

I am a former broadcaster, and I have called upon many of broadcasting colleagues to help with the cause. They have responded with overwhelming enthusiasm. But you do not need to be a broadcaster to be a part of the conversation. Pick up a mic, sit down with your neighbor and join the movement."
(http://occupytheairwaves.com/about)



